[{"id":"/sicpjs/3.1.1","tag":"TITLE","body":"3.1.1  \n    Local State Variables"},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p1","child":[{"body":"\n    To illustrate what we mean by having a computational object with\n    \n    time-varying state, let us model the situation of withdrawing money\n    from a\n    \n    bank account.  We will do this using a\n    function","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":", which takes as argument an\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"amount"},{"body":" to be withdrawn.\n    If there is enough money in the account to accommodate the withdrawal,\n    then ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" should return the balance\n    remaining after the withdrawal.  Otherwise,\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" should return the message\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"Insufficient funds.","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":" For example, if we begin with $100\n    in the account, we should obtain the following sequence of responses\n    using\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":":\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":1,"eval":true,"prependLength":11,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYEYEMA2uAdgMYCmIAvCKgAy1YAmZAZiAO4CWALgBaMAnXOwAUuALYB7AK5FuASgBcGEKpABzfJLz4QO4uRVrObfaQoA+ahJlzlah3oIGK1M+RABaEDdncjjiACZNzSAkROhOYBIGT4AM5k9oFBIWERAEQQRPHSLCycJJxkciAssozxGVgADgKcciJcfILCIgBMAKzy8kA","body":"print(withdraw(25)) ","output":"75"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":2,"eval":true,"prependLength":13,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYEYEMA2uAdgMYCmIAvCKgAy1YAmZAZiAO4CWALgBaMAnXOwAUuALYB7AK5FuASgBcGEKpABzfJLz4QO4uRVrObfaQoA+ahJlzlah3oIGK1M+RABaEDdncjjiACZNzSAkROhOYBIGT4AM5k9oFBIWERAEQQRPHSLCycJJxkciAssozxGVgADgKcciJcfILCIgBMAKzy8rX1jc38QqJdPUA","body":"print(withdraw(25)) ","output":"50"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":3,"eval":true,"prependLength":15,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYEYEMA2uAdgMYCmIAvCKgAy1YAmZAZiAO4CWALgBaMAnXOwAUuALYB7AK5FuASgBcGEKpABzfJLz4QO4uRVrObfaQoA+ahJlzlah3oIGK1M+RABaEDdncjjiACZNzSAkROhOYBIGT4AM5k9oFBIWERAEQQRPHSLCycJJxkciAssozxGVgADgKcciJcfILCIgBMAKzy8rX1jc38QqJdPX0N3E08Q20AbLQ9QA","body":"print(withdraw(60)) ","output":"\"Insufficient funds\""},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":4,"eval":true,"prependLength":17,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYEYEMA2uAdgMYCmIAvCKgAy1YAmZAZiAO4CWALgBaMAnXOwAUuALYB7AK5FuASgBcGEKpABzfJLz4QO4uRVrObfaQoA+ahJlzlah3oIGK1M+RABaEDdncjjiACZNzSAkROhOYBIGT4AM5k9oFBIWERAEQQRPHSLCycJJxkciAssozxGVgADgKcciJcfILCIgBMAKzy8rX1jc38QqJdPX0N3E08Q20AbLRjGHUTUy3DIqjd8kA","body":"print(withdraw(15)) ","output":"35"},{"body":"\n    Observe that the expression\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw(25)"},{"body":",\n      \n    evaluated twice, yields different values.  This is a new kind of\n    behavior for a\n    function.\n    Until now, all our\n    Python functions\n    could be viewed as specifications for computing mathematical functions.\n    A call to a\n    function\n    computed the value of the function applied to the given arguments,\n    and two calls to the same\n    function\n    with the same arguments always produced the same\n    result.","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-1","body":"1","href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#footnote-1"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p2","child":[{"body":"\n    To implement ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":", we can use a\n    variable ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" to indicate the balance of\n    money in the account and define ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":"\n    as a\n    function\n    that accesses ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":".\n    The ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":"function\n    checks to see if ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" is at least as large\n    as the requested ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"amount"},{"body":".  If so,\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" decrements\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" by ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"amount"},{"body":"\n    and returns the new value of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":". Otherwise,\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" returns the ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"Insufficient funds","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":"\n    message. Here are the\n    declarations\n    of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" and\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":":\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":5,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYEYEMA2uAdgMYCmIAvCKgAy1YAmZAZiAO4CWALgBaMAnXOwAUuALYB7AK5FuASgBcGEKpABzfJLz4QO4uRVrObfaQoA+ahJlzlah3oIGK1M+RABaEDdncjjiACZNzSAkROhOYBIGT4AM5k9oFBIWERAEQQRPHSLCycJJxkciAssozxGVgADgKcciJcfILCIgBMAKzy8kA","body":"balance = 100\n\ndef withdraw(amount):\n    global balance\n    if balance >= amount:\n        balance = balance - amount\n        return balance\n    else:\n        return \"Insufficient funds\" "},{"body":"\n    Decrementing ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" is accomplished by the \n    assignment","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":6,"eval":false,"body":"balance = balance - amount"},{"body":"\n\tThis statement looks like a declaration assignment, but it does\n\tnot declare a new variable. The global declaration\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":7,"eval":false,"body":"global balance"},{"body":"\n\tensures that the name\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" is already\n\tdeclared in the\tbody of the function \n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" \n\tand refers to the globally declared variable \n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":".\n\t\n\tAn assignment of the form\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":true,"eval":false,"body":"\n$name$ = $new$-$value$\n\t  "},{"body":"\n\twhere the ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"META","body":"name"},{"body":" is already declared, is called\n\ta ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"reassignment","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":".\n      The reassignment \n    changes\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"META","body":"name"},{"body":"\n    so that its value is the\n    result obtained by evaluating\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"META","body":"new-value"},{"body":".\n      \n    In the case at hand, we are changing ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" so\n    that its new value will be the result of subtracting\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"amount"},{"body":" from the previous value of\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":".","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-2","body":"2","href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#footnote-2"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p3","child":[{"body":"\n\tThe function ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" also uses a\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"sequence of statements","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":" to cause two statements to be evaluated\n\tin the case where the ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"if"},{"body":" test is\n\ttrue: first decrementing  ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":"\n\tand then returning the value of\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":".  \n\tIn general, executing a sequence\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":true,"eval":false,"body":"\n$stmt$$_{1}$ $stmt$$_{2} \\ldots$$stmt$$_{n}$\n          "},{"body":"\n        causes the statements ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"META","body":"stmt"},{"body":"$_{1}$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":"\n\tthrough\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"META","body":"stmt"},{"body":"$_{n}$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":" to be evaluated in\n\tsequence.","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-3","body":"3","href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#footnote-3"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p4","child":[{"body":"\n    Although ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" works as desired, the\n    variable ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" presents a problem.  As\n    specified above, ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" is a name defined\n    in the\n    program environment and is freely accessible to be examined or\n      modified by any\n      function.\n      It would be much better if we could somehow make\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" internal to\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":", so that\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" would be the only\n      function\n      that could access ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" directly and\n      any other\n      function\n      could access ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" only indirectly\n      (through calls to ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":").  This would\n      more accurately model the notion that\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" is a local state variable used by\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" to keep track of the state of the\n      account.\n  ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p5","child":[{"body":"\n    We can make ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" internal to\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" by rewriting the definition as\n    follows:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":8,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&","body":"def make_withdraw_balance_100():\n    balance = 100\n    def withdraw(amount):\n        nonlocal balance\n        if balance >= amount:\n            balance = balance - amount\n            return balance\n        else:\n            return \"Insufficient funds\"\n    return withdraw\n\nnew_withdraw = make_withdraw_balance_100() "},{"body":"\n        What we have done here is use a declaration assignment\n\tto establish an environment with a local variable\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":", bound to the initial\n\tvalue 100. Within this local environment, we use a function\n\tdeclaration to\n\tcreate a function\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" \n\tthat takes ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"amount"},{"body":"\n\tas an argument and—returned as the result of evaluating the body of the\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_withdraw_balance_100"},{"body":"\n\tfunction—behaves in precisely the same way as\n\tour previous\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" \n\tfunction,\n\tbut its variable\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" is not accessible by any\n\tother function.","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-4","body":"4","href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#footnote-4"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p6","child":[{"body":"\n\tThe nested ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":"\n\tfunction faces a similar problem as the previous\n\tglobal ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" function:\n\tThe assignment\n\tbalance = balance - amount\n\tshould refer to the variable balance declared outside\n\tof the ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" function,\n\tand should not redeclare the name\n\tbalance. However, now the name\n\tbalance is not a global name, but a name that is declared\n\tin the surrounding function\n\tmake_withdraw_balance_100.\n\tPython uses nonlocal declarations in this situation.\n\tThe declaration\n\tnonlocal balance\n\tin the nested withdraw function indicates that any assignment\n\tto the name balance inside the withdraw function refers\n\tto the variable balance declared outside the function\n\tbut not globally.","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-5","body":"5","href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#footnote-5"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p7","child":[{"body":"\n    Combining \n    \n        reassignments with declaration assignments\n      \n    is the general programming\n    technique we will use for constructing computational objects with\n    local state.  Unfortunately, using this technique raises a serious\n    problem: When we first introduced\n    functions,\n    we also introduced the substitution model of evaluation\n    (section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"1.1.5","href":"/sicpjs/1.1.5"},{"body":") to provide an\n    interpretation of what\n    function\n    application means.  We said that applying a\n    function whose body is a return statement\n    should be interpreted as evaluating the\n    return expression of the function\n    with the\n    \n    parameters replaced by their values.\n    \n\tFor functions with more complex\n\tbodies, we need to evaluate the whole body with the\n\tparameters replaced by their values.\n      \n    The trouble is that,\n    as soon as we introduce assignment into our language, substitution is no\n    longer an adequate model of\n    function\n    application.  (We will see why this is so in\n    section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"3.1.3","href":"/sicpjs/3.1.3"},{"body":".)  As a consequence, we\n    technically have at this point no way to understand why the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"new_withdraw"},{"body":"function\n    behaves as claimed above.  In order to really understand a\n    function\n    such as\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"new_withdraw"},{"body":",\n      \n    we will need to develop a new model of\n    function\n    application.  In section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"3.2","href":"/sicpjs/3.2"},{"body":" we will\n    introduce such a model, together with an explanation of \n    reassignment statements and declaration assignments.\n    First, however, we examine some variations on the theme established by\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"new_withdraw"},{"body":".\n      ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p8","child":[{"body":"\n    The following\n    \n\tfunction, ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_withdraw"},{"body":",\n      \n    creates \"","tag":"#text"},{"body":"withdrawal processors.","tag":"#text"},{"body":"\"\n    The  parameter\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" in\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_withdraw"},{"body":"\n    specifies the initial amount of money in the\n    account.","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-6","body":"6","href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#footnote-6"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":9,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYCYFMBmIAtgIYDWuA+gO4CWALgBbYBOJ1AFAEYkA2JAOwDGuAJQAuDCGkg8hOk1bsOJIgHsArgPoSpM-QLUDeaoXxA9+w3Hv3TahS4JEgAfAF4Qqzdsl3-FnzOuCCeTtYgALRe6lr0tgHSLLj0GiwCgVYiCfq4vADOuH6JMsmp6SAARBAC+Rr4+LRCtLjaIPha2PmVCWVpGQrMbNRYAOqoocTkVINKnKgADAuiGKMATJOkFDQMQ8qLy0A","body":"def make_withdraw(balance):\n    def withdraw(amount):\n        nonlocal balance\n        if balance >= amount:\n            balance = balance - amount\n            return balance\n        else:\n            return \"Insufficient funds\"\n    return withdraw "},{"body":"\n\tThe function ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_withdraw"},{"body":"\n    can be used as follows to create two objects ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"W1"},{"body":"\n    and ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"W2"},{"body":":\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":10,"eval":true,"prependLength":11,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYCYFMBmIAtgIYDWuA+gO4CWALgBbYBOJ1AFAEYkA2JAOwDGuAJQAuDCGkg8hOk1bsOJIgHsArgPoSpM-QLUDeaoXxA9+w3Hv3TahS4JEgAfAF4Qqzdsl3-FnzOuCCeTtYgALRe6lr0tgHSLLj0GiwCgVYiCfq4vADOuH6JMsmp6SAARBAC+Rr4+LRCtLjaIPha2PmVCWVpGQrMbNRYAOqoocTkVINKnKgADAuiGKMATJOkFDQMQ8qLy0A","body":"W1 = make_withdraw(100)\nW2 = make_withdraw(100) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":11,"eval":true,"prependLength":14,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYCYFMBmIAtgIYDWuA+gO4CWALgBbYBOJ1AFAEYkA2JAOwDGuAJQAuDCGkg8hOk1bsOJIgHsArgPoSpM-QLUDeaoXxA9+w3Hv3TahS4JEgAfAF4Qqzdsl3-FnzOuCCeTtYgALRe6lr0tgHSLLj0GiwCgVYiCfq4vADOuH6JMsmp6SAARBAC+Rr4+LRCtLjaIPha2PmVCWVpGQrMbNRYAOqoocTkVINKnKgADAuiGKMATJOkFDQMQ8qLy1gADiy02hzjHACsy6JAA","body":"print(W1(50)) ","output":"50"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":12,"eval":true,"prependLength":16,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYCYFMBmIAtgIYDWuA+gO4CWALgBbYBOJ1AFAEYkA2JAOwDGuAJQAuDCGkg8hOk1bsOJIgHsArgPoSpM-QLUDeaoXxA9+w3Hv3TahS4JEgAfAF4Qqzdsl3-FnzOuCCeTtYgALRe6lr0tgHSLLj0GiwCgVYiCfq4vADOuH6JMsmp6SAARBAC+Rr4+LRCtLjaIPha2PmVCWVpGQrMbNRYAOqoocTkVINKnKgADAuiGKMATJOkFDQMQ8qLy1gADiy02hzjHACsyysYJ2f0F2scAOy3QA","body":"print(W2(70)) ","output":"30"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":13,"eval":true,"prependLength":18,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYCYFMBmIAtgIYDWuA+gO4CWALgBbYBOJ1AFAEYkA2JAOwDGuAJQAuDCGkg8hOk1bsOJIgHsArgPoSpM-QLUDeaoXxA9+w3Hv3TahS4JEgAfAF4Qqzdsl3-FnzOuCCeTtYgALRe6lr0tgHSLLj0GiwCgVYiCfq4vADOuH6JMsmp6SAARBAC+Rr4+LRCtLjaIPha2PmVCWVpGQrMbNRYAOqoocTkVINKnKgADAuiGKMATJOkFDQMQ8qLy1gADiy02hzjHACsyysYJ2f0F2scAOy3x6fn6xwALLdAA","body":"print(W2(40)) ","output":"\"Insufficient funds\""},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":14,"eval":true,"prependLength":20,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYCYFMBmIAtgIYDWuA+gO4CWALgBbYBOJ1AFAEYkA2JAOwDGuAJQAuDCGkg8hOk1bsOJIgHsArgPoSpM-QLUDeaoXxA9+w3Hv3TahS4JEgAfAF4Qqzdsl3-FnzOuCCeTtYgALRe6lr0tgHSLLj0GiwCgVYiCfq4vADOuH6JMsmp6SAARBAC+Rr4+LRCtLjaIPha2PmVCWVpGQrMbNRYAOqoocTkVINKnKgADAuiGKMATJOkFDQMQ8qLy1gADiy02hzjHACsyysYJ2f0F2scAOy3x6fn6xwALB-3L5PS7-USiIA","body":"print(W1(40)) ","output":"10"},{"body":"\n    Observe that ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"W1"},{"body":" and \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"W2"},{"body":" are completely independent objects, each\n    with its own local state variable ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":".\n    Withdrawals from one do not affect the other.\n  ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p9","child":[{"body":"\n    We can also create objects that handle\n    \n    deposits as well as\n    withdrawals, and thus we can represent simple bank accounts.  Here is\n    a\n    function\n    that returns a \"","tag":"#text"},{"body":"bank-account object","tag":"#text"},{"body":"\" with a specified initial\n    balance:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":15,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&-BT-dQs9gAVhlQiAA","body":"def make_account(balance):\n    def withdraw(amount):\n        nonlocal balance\n        if balance >= amount:\n            balance = balance - amount\n            return balance\n        else:\n            return \"Insufficient funds\"\n    def deposit(amount):\n        nonlocal balance\n        balance = balance + amount\n        return balance\n    def dispatch(m):\n        return (withdraw if m == \"withdraw\"\n                else deposit if m == \"deposit\"\n                else error(m, \"unknown request -- make_account\"))\n    return dispatch "},{"body":"\n    Each call to ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_account"},{"body":" sets up an\n    environment with a local state variable ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":".\n    Within this environment, ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_account"},{"body":" defines\n    functions","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"deposit"},{"body":" and\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" that access\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" and an additional\n    function","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"dispatch"},{"body":"\n    that takes a \"","tag":"#text"},{"body":"message","tag":"#text"},{"body":"\" as input and returns one of the two local\n    functions.\n    The ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"dispatch"},{"body":"function\n    itself is returned as the value that represents the bank-account object.\n    This is precisely the \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"message-passing","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":" style of programming that we saw in\n    section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"2.4.3","href":"/sicpjs/2.4.3"},{"body":", although here we are using\n    it in conjunction with the ability to modify local variables.\n  ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p10","child":[{"body":"\n\tThe function\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_account"},{"body":"\n    can be used as follows:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":16,"eval":true,"prependLength":19,"program":"chap=3&","body":"acc = make_account(100) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":17,"eval":true,"prependLength":21,"program":"chap=3&-BT-dQs9gAVhlQiAA","body":"print(acc(\"withdraw\")(50)) ","output":"50"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":18,"eval":true,"prependLength":23,"program":"chap=3&-BT-dQs9gAVhlsvlio4AtVfzegKE7AAbHqgA","body":"print(acc(\"withdraw\")(60)) ","output":"\"Insufficient funds\""},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":19,"eval":true,"prependLength":25,"program":"chap=3&-BT-dQs9gAVhlsvlio4AtVfzegKE7AAbHqsAalcaqgiRkiLQAWPVAA","body":"print(acc(\"deposit\")(40)) ","output":"90"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":20,"eval":true,"prependLength":27,"program":"chap=3&-BT-dQs9gAVhlsvlio4AtVfzegKE7AAbHqsAalcaqgiRkiLQAWG1yhX2lVq14ArXW1lAA","body":"print(acc(\"withdraw\")(60)) ","output":"30"},{"body":"\n    Each call to ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"acc"},{"body":" returns the locally defined\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"deposit"},{"body":" or ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":"function,\n    which is then applied to the specified ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"amount"},{"body":".\n    As was the case with\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_withdraw"},{"body":", another\n\tcall to ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_account"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":21,"eval":true,"prependLength":19,"program":"chap=3&","body":"acc2 = make_account(100) "},{"body":"\n    will produce a completely separate account object, which maintains its\n    own local ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":".\n  ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 3.1","id":"#ex-3.1","child":[{"body":"\n    An \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"accumulator","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":" is a\n    function\n    that is called repeatedly with a single numeric argument and accumulates its\n    arguments into a sum. Each time it is called, it returns the currently\n    accumulated sum. Write a\n    function","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_accumulator"},{"body":"\n    that generates accumulators, each maintaining an independent sum.  The\n    input to \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_accumulator"},{"body":"\n    should specify the initial value of the sum; for example\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":22,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAdAWwIYDWApgPp4DG5ArjlQDZ4AuA9gE4gsgBGRIA7qwCWjRkQB23BAGdGVACbjGUjHhABeEPmJlKNekzYAKAKwBKIA","body":"a = make_accumulator(5) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":23,"eval":true,"prependLength":4,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAdAWwIYDWApgPp4DG5ArjlQDZ4AuA9gE4gsgBGRIA7qwCWjRkQB23BAGdGVACbjGUjHhABeEPmJlKNekzYAKAKwBKLAAchYxobyHUABlOmgA","body":"print(a(10)) ","output":"15"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":24,"eval":true,"prependLength":6,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAdAWwIYDWApgPp4DG5ArjlQDZ4AuA9gE4gsgBGRIA7qwCWjRkQB23BAGdGVACbjGUjHhABeEPmJlKNekzYAKAKwBKLAAchYxobyHUABlPmMVwTbsPnpoA","body":"print(a(10)) ","output":"25"}],"solution":[{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":25,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYCYFMBmIAtgIYDWuA+iQMY0CuR9ANiQC4D2ATgBQNddcAOzYBKAFwYQ0kHkIls2HiS4BzCVJlahHIcw40SzEP0EjNW6aeFsQAXhP0BNkAGoQK1RcuC2ToY7O5lq+-h6KWCT2xORUtAxMrJy8AKyiGCQ8qAAM6QAOXACWIspZuaJAA","body":"def make_accumulator(current):\n    def add(arg):\n        nonlocal current\n        current = current + arg\n        return current\n    return add "}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 3.2","id":"#ex-3.2","child":[{"body":"\n    In software-testing applications, it is useful to be able to count the\n    number of times a given\n    function\n    is called during the course of a computation.  Write a\n    function","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_monitored"},{"body":"\n    that takes as input a\n    function,","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"f"},{"body":", that itself takes one input.  The result\n    returned by \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_monitored"},{"body":"\n    is a third\n    function,\n    say ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"mf"},{"body":", that keeps track of the number of times\n    it has been called by maintaining an internal counter. If the input to\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"mf"},{"body":" is the\n    string ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"\"how many calls\""},{"body":",\n      \n    then ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"mf"},{"body":" returns the value of the counter.  If\n    the input is the \n    string ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"\"reset count\""},{"body":",\n      \n    then ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"mf"},{"body":" resets the counter to zero.  For any\n    other input, ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"mf"},{"body":" returns the result of calling\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"f"},{"body":" on that input and increments the counter.\n    For instance, we could make a monitored version of the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"sqrt"},{"body":"function:","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":26,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAdAWwIYDWApgPo4D2AdgJYAu5ATkQCYgBmArpQMa3VUh6IAEZEQAdwZ1aRSiIQBnWh2azaCjApABeEPmJkqdRiwAU+WgAsSCgI4NaASiA","body":"s = make_monitored(math_sqrt) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":27,"eval":true,"prependLength":4,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAdAWwIYDWApgPo4D2AdgJYAu5ATkQCYgBmArpQMa3VUh6IAEZEQAdwZ1aRSiIQBnWh2azaCjApABeEPmJkqdRiwAU+WgAsSCgI4NaASiwAHKZVqmFp1AAZfjo5AA","body":"print(s(100)) ","output":"10"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":28,"eval":true,"prependLength":6,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAdAWwIYDWApgPo4D2AdgJYAu5ATkQCYgBmArpQMa3VUh6IAEZEQAdwZ1aRSiIQBnWh2azaCjApABeEPmJkqdRiwAU+WgAsSCgI4NaASiwAHKZVqmFp1AAZfjs4YbtQeXqYARJbk4np4lAjceAA2yQoRgUA","body":"print(s(\"how many calls\")) ","output":"1"}],"solution":[{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":29,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYM4gLwgC2AhgNYCmA+oQPYB2AlgC40BO5AJgBQlMAWlbAEdWTAJQ4uqAAzSJAB1YM6TLti4AiPjQDuRYnQQBjYgBtT2DWInqArAqUq1m7XpKGQJ85etA","body":"s = make_monitored(math_sqrt)\ns(100)\nprint(s(\"how many calls\"))\ns(5)\nprint(s(\"how many calls\")) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":30,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&-hUTE4qJtMkQjxHpwAKwfL5SX6cf7RUhAhKg8FAA","body":"def make_monitored(f):\n    counter = 0  # initialized to 0\n    def mf(cmd):\n        nonlocal counter\n        if cmd == \"how many calls\":\n            return counter\n        elif cmd == \"reset count\":\n            counter = 0\n            return counter\n        else:\n            counter = counter + 1\n            return f(cmd)\n    return mf "}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 3.3","id":"#ex-3.3","child":[{"body":"\n    Modify the \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_account"},{"body":"function\n    so that it creates\n    \n    password-protected accounts.  That is, \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_account"},{"body":"\n    should take a\n    string\n    as an additional argument, as in\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":31,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAdAWwIYDWApgPp4DG5A9gK4B2ALiAGb3kMCWVdIDVIAIyIgA7gCcODBkR4CEAZwY0AJjIbyMFciAC8IfMTKVajABSoADBYA0IAETyi5MUSYAHPPPkiqY5XYBKIA","body":"acc = make_account(100, \"secret password\") "},{"body":"\n    The resulting account object should process a request only if it is\n    accompanied by the password with which the account was created, and\n    should otherwise return a complaint:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":32,"eval":true,"prependLength":4,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAdAWwIYDWApgPp4DG5A9gK4B2ALiAGb3kMCWVdIDVIAIyIgA7gCcODBkR4CEAZwY0AJjIbyMFciAC8IfMTKVajABSoADBYA0IAETyi5MUSYAHPPPkiqY5XYBKLDcJMy1TBycXd09vX39bOxFJAAtlMTwRQNMAFgsAgKA","body":"print(acc(\"secret password\", \"withdraw\")(40)) ","output":"60"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":33,"eval":true,"prependLength":6,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAdAWwIYDWApgPp4DG5A9gK4B2ALiAGb3kMCWVdIDVIAIyIgA7gCcODBkR4CEAZwY0AJjIbyMFciAC8IfMTKVajABSoADBYA0IAETyi5MUSYAHPPPkiqY5XYBKLDcJMy1TBycXd09vX39bOxFJAAtlMTwRQNMAFgsAoIwQjjDKCPkqHGEqBhSiMRAPLx8-O0TVNyp5SWy8gqA","body":"print(acc(\"some other password\", \"deposit\")(40)) ","output":"\"Incorrect password\""}],"solution":[{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":34,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=MQAgygkgwgCgniAzAOgIxoFAYCYFMBmIAtgIYDWuA+iQMY0D2ArgHYAuAFAEYkA2JzNXABoQABwCUALgwhZIPIQDuAS1YALbACcSi9iSJM2UmXNPN6zHvRq8Q3PgNwnTs5YXv9BIAHwBeEPqGrNIuoXa8nrgg-h6OIAC0AQYsrM5hspq4rIyazOEOgmmmuDwAzrgh6XKZ2bkgAEQQzKWM+PjKNMq4bCD4LNil9WkK8rii9KWqeslGlaHmlta2sYXpK1ExEXEA1ElBRdVZOXnrwwTyyqWiJKw0auxEIgCOxuluYtH+T3NVNccg7BU6i0OhA7yInwaQI02kUQyqCJAJXKo3Gk1YYMIEN8-nqeDRqnhiPSyKi9QAqswyOZFHlMk9GLhSsFiOQqLQGCl6uIDrJST90n86nwiJxsCQQN8Gk0GJpMjQMTASKVSop6JpsESMkc6thLtdbmosBL-KQKNQ6EF2KgAAw2kT1XAANxI3IwJHY9WhILhDudrvE7AArDbxLJQN7YaUQCGMKJNMo2HpPZGdPUHZxutz2AAWUNhkCgROy+UY64qtUaoA","body":"def make_account(balance, p):\n    def withdraw(amount):\n        nonlocal balance\n        if balance >= amount:\n            balance = balance - amount\n            return balance\n        else:\n            return \"Insufficient funds\"\n    def deposit(amount):\n        nonlocal balance\n        balance = balance + amount\n        return balance\n    def dispatch(m, q):\n        if p == q:\n            return (withdraw if m == \"withdraw\"\n                    else deposit if m == \"deposit\"\n                    else \"Unknown request: make_account\")\n        else:\n            return lambda q: \"Incorrect Password\"\n    return dispatch\n\na = make_account(100, \"eva\")\na(\"withdraw\", \"eva\")(50)  # withdraws 50\nprint(a(\"withdraw\", \"ben\")(40))  # incorrect password "}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 3.4","id":"#ex-3.4","child":[{"body":"\n    Modify the \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_account"},{"body":"function\n    of exercise ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"3.3","href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#ex-3.3"},{"body":" by adding another\n    local state variable so that, if an account is accessed more than seven\n    consecutive times with an incorrect password, it invokes the\n    function","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"call_the_cops"},{"body":".\n      ","tag":"#text"}],"solution":[{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":35,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&-XUjRQ6ECuZUgMYgJiEfAkVRkdXXdKZbKIoQs1GqNgsNJEWgcZwRACOgpGBKJ5DiAkSHJSaQyWRyOsWhASSWjDrjBg2IAA7N9dcLiOQOZoxbz2AmQB8lpEKfl--yXMC9zrLCryIt85yVxi4KPPioRvMigLuiCnT0vCny-Jyiy0riwqXRYLh1H8Yroty2LQoqoQgA","body":"def call_the_cops(reason):\n    return \"calling the cops because \" + reason\n\ndef make_account(balance, p):\n\n    invalid_attempts = 0  # initializes to 0\n\n    def withdraw(amount):\n        nonlocal balance\n        if balance >= amount:\n            balance = balance - amount\n            return balance\n        else:\n            return \"Insufficient funds\"\n\n    def deposit(amount):\n        nonlocal balance\n        balance = balance + amount\n        return balance\n\n    def calling_the_cops(_):\n        return call_the_cops(\"you have exceeded \" +\n                             \"the max no of failed attempts\")\n\n    def dispatch(m, q):\n        nonlocal invalid_attempts\n        if invalid_attempts > 7:\n            return calling_the_cops\n        elif p == q:\n            invalid_attempts = 0  # reset after a correct password\n            return (withdraw if m == \"withdraw\"\n                    else deposit if m == \"deposit\"\n                    else \"Unknown request: make_account\")\n        else:\n            invalid_attempts = invalid_attempts + 1\n            if invalid_attempts > 7:\n                return calling_the_cops\n            else:\n                return lambda x: \"Incorrect Password\"\n\n    return dispatch "}]},{"tag":"DISPLAYFOOTNOTE","id":"#footnote-1","count":1,"href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#footnote-link-1","child":[{"body":"Actually, this is not quite true. One exception was the \n    \n    random-number generator\n    in section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"1.2.6","href":"/sicpjs/1.2.6"},{"body":".  Another exception\n    involved the\n    \n    operation/type tables we introduced in\n    section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"2.4.3","href":"/sicpjs/2.4.3"},{"body":", where the values of two\n    calls to ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"get"},{"body":" with the same arguments\n    depended on intervening calls to ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"put"},{"body":".\n    On the other hand, until we introduce\n    reassignment,\n    we have no way to\n    create such\n    functions\n    ourselves.","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"DISPLAYFOOTNOTE","id":"#footnote-2","count":2,"href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#footnote-link-2","child":[{"body":"\n\tReassignment statements and declaration assignments\n\tlook similar to and should not be confused with\n\t\n\texpressions of the form \n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":true,"eval":false,"body":"\n$expression_1$ == $expression_2$\n          "},{"body":"\n\twhich evaluate to ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"True"},{"body":"\n\tif ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"META","body":"expression"},{"body":"$_1$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":" evaluates to the\n\tsame value as ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"META","body":"expression"},{"body":"$_2$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":" and to\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"False"},{"body":" otherwise.\n      ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"DISPLAYFOOTNOTE","id":"#footnote-3","count":3,"href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#footnote-link-3","child":[{"body":"We have already used \n        \n        sequences implicitly in our programs, because in\n\tPython the body block\n\tof a function can contain a sequence of function definitions\n\tfollowed by a return statement, not\n\tjust a single return statement,\n\tas discussed in\n\tsection ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"1.1.8","href":"/sicpjs/1.1.8"},{"body":".","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"DISPLAYFOOTNOTE","id":"#footnote-4","count":4,"href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#footnote-link-4","child":[{"body":"In programming-language jargon, the variable\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" is said to be \n        ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"encapsulated","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":" within the\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"new_withdraw"},{"body":" function.\n\tEncapsulation reflects the general system-design principle known as the \n        ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"hiding principle","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":": One can\n        make a system more modular and robust by protecting parts of the\n        system from each other; that is, by providing information access only\n        to those parts of the system that have a \"","tag":"#text"},{"body":"need to\n\tknow.","tag":"#text"},{"body":"\"","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"DISPLAYFOOTNOTE","id":"#footnote-5","count":5,"href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#footnote-link-5","child":[{"body":"\n\tSimilar to global declarations, \n\ta nonlocal declaration does not extend to functions that\n\tare nested inside the function in which the nonlocal declaration\n\tappears. For these nested functions to reassign the\n\tnonlocal variable, they also need to declare the variable as nonlocal.\n\t","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"DISPLAYFOOTNOTE","id":"#footnote-6","count":6,"href":"/sicpjs/3.1.1#footnote-link-6","child":[{"body":"\n    In contrast with\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"make_withdraw_balance_100"},{"body":"\n    above, we do not have to use\n    \n\ta declaration assignment\n      \n    to make ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"PYTHONINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" a local variable, since\n    \n    parameters are already\n    local. This will be clearer after the discussion of the environment\n    model of evaluation in\n    section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"3.2","href":"/sicpjs/3.2"},{"body":".\n    (See also\n    exercise ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"3.10","href":"/sicpjs/3.2.3#ex-3.10"},{"body":".)","tag":"#text"}]}]